  "text": "PLG matrices were fabricated, as described [CITATION_1] , to coordinate the recruitment and anti-tumor programming of dendritic cells via the controlled presentation of tumor lysates with GM-CSF and CpG-rich ODN (PLG vaccines). In mice bearing 3-day-old B16 melanoma tumors (5x10 5 cells), treatment with CTLA-4 and PD-1 antibodies alone have no effect on tumor progression and survival outcomes in these animals ( Supplementary   Fig. S1 ). Moreover, a single PLG vaccination modestly suppressed tumor progression but did not effect long-term survival in any mice bearing B16 melanoma tumors (Fig. 1) .",
